# Web Project Rules

## Stack (this project)
- Vanilla HTML5, CSS (BEM-like), ES6+ JS. Data: localStorage + JSON export/import. No React/Vue, no backend.

## Code
- **SOLID/KISS/DRY/YAGNI**: One responsibility per function, no duplication, no "for future" code.
- **Clean Code**: Descriptive names, functions &lt;20 lines, named constants instead of magic numbers.
- **JS**: ES6+, no jQuery. Minimal global state; small pure helpers (uid, formatDate, etc.).

## Frontend
- **HTML**: Semantic tags (`header`, `main`, `section`, `nav`), `lang`, ARIA where needed (`role`, `aria-label`, `aria-modal`).
- **CSS**: BEM-style classes, design tokens in `:root`. No inline styles. Mobile-first; test from 320px.
- **A11y**: Skip link, keyboard nav, `alt` for images, focus visible.

## Output
- Generate full file (imports + export) when adding files.
- Describe how the change looks in the browser when UI is touched.
- Deploy-ready: keep `netlify.toml` or `vercel.json` valid.
